{"insight":"You Were Held Before You Began","publicTitle":"Held Before We Begin","plainSummary":"Some help is not earned by strength; it is noticed when proving ourselves no longer rules us.","atAGlance":"Lonely people often learn to turn every gift into proof that they can stand alone. The path begins by noticing what already carries us. A teacher, promise, community, simple act, or trusted hand can steady the first step before we own it. The danger is turning even surrender into another private win.","keyPoints":["Meaning can begin with receiving, not proving.","Isolation deepens when help becomes another test of worth.","Test whether help lowers striving or becomes another trophy."],"match":["the road starts before you"],"tags":["help","loneliness","practice"]}
